http://www.thehindu.com/news/national/karnataka/CESC-officials-unearth-power-stealing/article13998591.ece

The vigilance squad of Chamundeshwari Electricity Supply Corporation (CESC) has detected electricity being stolen by an event organiser at Sir M. Visvesvaraya District Stadium here and imposed a fine of Rs. 21,944 for the offence. N. Jayakumar had organised an event at the stadium, recently.Direct hookingHowever, he was allegedly stealing power directly (hooking) from the nearby electricity pole, a senior CESC official told The Hindu. A team, led by Assistant Executive Officer Shivakrishna, raided the place at about 11.45 p.m. on January 7 and seized the cables.Later, a case was booked against the accused under the Electricity Act, 2003, he said.